Noble Township is one of seven townships in Wabash County, Indiana, USA. As of the 2000 census, its population was 15,580.1
Geography
According to the United States Census Bureau, Noble Township covers an area of ; of this,  (99.41 percent) is land and  (0.59 percent) is water.
